  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In the same train going to Concord was Chief Justice S. P. Chase. William Lloyd Garrison elaborates on S. P. Chase: &quot;I did not care to speak to him--partly because of his enfeebled condition, and partly because I have long since lost much of the respect I had for him.&quot; Garrison was met by George A. Blanchard in Concord. There was a severe thunderstorm that night. He tells about Mrs. Blanchard&apos;s 43rd birthday party. Garrison will go on some sightseeing tours.</subfield>
